# This agent supports two LLM backends. Configure one of the following:
#
# Option 1 — GitHub Copilot model (quickest start):
#   Set GITHUB_TOKEN to a fine-grained PAT with "Copilot Requests → Read-only".
#   Create one at: https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
#   Classic tokens (ghp_) are not supported — use github_pat_, gho_, or ghu_ tokens.
#
# Option 2 — Bring your own Foundry model (BYOK):
#   Set FOUNDRY_PROJECT_ENDPOINT and AZURE_AI_MODEL_DEPLOYMENT_NAME.
#   No GITHUB_TOKEN needed — authenticates via Managed Identity.
#   FOUNDRY_PROJECT_ENDPOINT is auto-injected when deployed as a hosted agent.
#
# If both are set, the Foundry model takes precedence.

GITHUB_TOKEN=
# FOUNDRY_PROJECT_ENDPOINT=https://<account>.services.ai.azure.com/api/projects/<project>
# AZURE_AI_MODEL_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=gpt-4o

# Optional — session ID for persistence/resume across restarts.
# If unset, a random UUID is generated per process.
# FOUNDRY_AGENT_SESSION_ID=
